National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice released a statement expressing her deep sadness over the passing of Samuel R. "Sandy" Berger, her predecessor. She describes Berger as a remarkable man who was funny, warm, passionate, brilliant, and loyal. Rice acknowledges the immense impact Berger had on foreign policy, nurturing and mentoring a whole generation of experts and practitioners. She personally credits him for her own knowledge and continued guidance. Rice also highlights the positive effects of Berger's work on international relations with countries like Japan, India, China, and Africa. She extends her condolences to Berger's family and emphasizes that his legacy will live on through his contributions to the country and the world.